description:
The magnitude 7.8 earthquake, which killed more than 7500 people and affected more than 8 million, has wiped out entire villages and destroyed a vast amount of infrastructure.Aid agencies estimate that between 50 and 70 per cent of community health facilities have been destroyed in affected regions.To make matters worse, the monsoon season is coming and hundreds of thousands of people are homeless. With the rains will come lack of shelter and increased risk of disease outbreaks.Rebuilding basic infrastructure will be difficult for Nepal, one of the poorest countries in Asia."Should the humanitarian response falter for lack of funds or any other reason, it threatens to reverse decades of progress improving the lives of Nepalese families and communities, and especially for mothers and children."
